values: So on Monday I have an interview to get into the radiology program at HCC and I am so nervous about it because if I don't get in then I don't know what I'm going to do. It sucks because there is no one that I can really talk to who really understands. Everyone can say "you'll be fine and you'll get in" but it still makes me nervous. There is always someone that is better than you. That's the part that scares me the most. In a couple weeks this will all be over and I'll finally know once and for all if I'll have to choose another career or not...

A heart as pure as gold.
Meanness not in your soul.
A smile for everyone, even me.
I could just call out your name,
and you'd be there.
I made the mistake of loving you,
and God took you away,
but now I know he only takes the best.
Just looking at your picture
reminds me of that.
I wish I could see you one more time
so I could say I love you
and goodbye.
And to tell you that when God
took you away from me,
a piece of me died that day.
I hate that feeling when you know that nothing is ever going to be the same again. It's so hard to lose someone you love so much... I'm going to really miss my Uncle Fred... 7/30/06

I haven't updated in a while, so.... Tuesday Adam and I went to Boston. It was so much fun. We took the T into Boston and neither of us knew what stop was for Quincy market. I hadn't been in so long so we took a guess and we were right! lol. After we had been there for a little while we had lunch at a seafood restaurant that was really good. We still had a lot of time to kill until the Red Sox game, so we decided to go to the aquarium. That was pretty cool because I had never been there before. After that it was about time to go to the game so we took the T to Fenway. It was such a great day. To top it all off... the Red Sox won!!! It was the best trip to Boston that I had ever had!!!

Wow the sun actually came out today!! This rain has become very depressing. I'm so excited that school is almost done. I have one more class on Thursday and then I am officially on summer vacation!!! I can't wait until next month because Adam and I are going to a Red Sox game. I like watching them on tv, but I love going to the games. I'm so excited!!!!

My love, you know you are my best friend. 
You know that I'd do anything for you 
And my love, let nothing come between us. 
My love for you is strong and true.

Sometimes I miss the way things used to be when I was little, when I used to ride my bike around until my mom told me to come in because it was starting to get dark. Everything was so simple then.... Days like today always make me miss those times...
I can honestly say that I have never felt like this before... :(
This was the best friday that I have had in the longest time..... :) It was way better than sitting at home doing homework....

I'm so sick of my car... why can't I have a week where I don't have any problems with it? And in the next couple weeks I'm going to have to get it fixed because it's been making funny noises and I know that's gonna cost me at least $500.
Thanks Adam for a great Valentine's Day!!! :)
Love is an irresistible desire to be irresistibly desired.
So has anyone seen the picture of Britney Spears holding her baby while driving? I saw it and that's why people like her should not be allowed to have kids.

So I started school again... that's all I'm going to say about that because I hate it so much. Everything else is still kind of the same... not too much excitement as usual. How many more months til summer vacation anyway?

I'm sooooo unbelivably sick of sitting at home...  It's the last weekend of vacation and everyone else is out having a good time and what am I doing... sitting at home wishing I was anywhere but here...
So I'm getting my wisdom teeth out tomorrow and I'm not even nervous yet... the only thing that I am really worried about is my face swelling up and making me look completely scary...
my life sucks so much right now...
I'm all done school!!!! I am so excited that I don't have to get up early and walk to class.... The best part of all is that it's almost Christmas...
People seriously need to chill out, take a deep breathe and realize life is too short to bitch about every little thing that happens...

Nothing new has happened lately. Last Saturday was my birthday and I am now 20. Adam took me to the Olive Garden because it is my favorite restaurant. Mostly because I love pasta. lol! I got a new sweater, a sweatshirt, and the movie March of the Penguins from Adam. <3 I love that movie eventhough it's a documentary, but it doesn't seem like that when you watch it. The baby penguins are the cutest thing ever! I also got a new purse from my sister which I love, movie passes from my brother and scratch tickets which I lost on. It was a really good birthday! I got everything that I wanted. I can't believe that Christmas is in a few weeks! I'm only half way through my christmas shopping. I still have about 4 or 5 more people to shop for and those are the hardest people to shop for. I have to get really creative!!! But I have to say that this is my favorite time of the year!!!
how do you fix a broken Christmas Tree?
HAPPY BIRTHDAY ADAM... I LOVE YOU!!!! <FONT color=#ff0000><3</FONT>

It's been a rough night. I couldn't sleep so I woke up at 7 to try and do some homework before I go to work at 10:30. I hate going to work on days like these. I'm hoping that it will be quick and painless because I'll be out at 3. I really wish that things didn't always end up the same way on the weekend. I end up doing the same thing every single day... I would much rather hang out with my friends, who I don't get to spend as much time with because of school and work. But that's going to change very soon. Vacation is coming and I'm not going to sit home and do nothing I'm going to go out and enjoy every single day no matter what happens. I really hate school right now!!!

Have you ever thought that people would be a lot happier if you were never brought into their lives?because that's how I feel right now... :(

So after spending 600 dollars on my car and having to listen to it squeal for a week apparently I need a new altenator... I haven't even had this car for a year yet and I have already had to put so much money into it... I think this car is going to leave me broke
who wants to waste their time writing two 5 page papers anyway... I certainly don't!!

Have you ever woke up one morning and asked yourself... does my life have a purpose? Because I have come to the conclusion that my life does not have a purpose whatsoever. I haven't accomplished anything great and I probably never will. I go to college where I am majoring in liberal arts... what am I going to do with that? I feel like I'm walking on earth just taking up space that someone who has ambition to do something with their life deserves. I feel that at this point in my life I am never going to amount to anything and that I'll go through life never finding my true calling. For most people it's no problem fromt he moment that they are born, they know exactly what they want to do. As for me I can't say that same.

My whole plan today was to sleep til about 10 then get up and do all the work that I need to do today. But at five of eight this morning my phone rings... it's my brother. He forgot his paper for his class so he needs me to get out of my warm bed, which I wasn't planning on leaving until 10, and go down to the computer and send it to him. I couldn't even find it so I had to look around for it. I'm wide awake now so I don't think I can go back to bed now. :( The next time that I need to do something for him he better not complain because he owes me now!

I should be doing something constructive.... whatever! Life has been pretty much the same lately. Tomorrow should be fun though... Lizzy is coming home for the weekend and we are going to hang out all day. We haven't done that in a long time and I'm really looking forward to it. I have to go to school for 2:30 today and then after that I have 5 day weekend! I'm so excited I can't wait. But of course I have a test on Wednesday in my Zoology Lab so I bet everyone can guess what I will be doing on Sunday and Monday. Boring!!
Plans change... I guess it's gonna be an early night!

I hate doing homework... it's such a waste of my time!!! Anyways Thank God it's Friday... I don't have to go to school again until Tuesday! Hopefully tonight I will have something to do. But right now I think I'm hanging out with Anna and whoever else comes with us. It should be fun. But my life is boring and I don't have very much to say. 

I hope the Red Sox beat the Yankees tonight!

So a year ago today, Adam asked me out for the first time. It's hard to believe that a whole year has gone by already...


HAPPY ANNIVERSARY!!! I Love You!

I went to the Big E on Wednesday with Adam, it was fun. We walked around and went to see the animals. Adam liked them more than I did but it was still cool. The only thing that I wanted to see were the hatching baby chicks. They were so cute! I also had my first Maine baked potato. It was good... I never had one from the Maine building before because the line was always so crazy but it wasn't too bad the other day. School has been okay lately... it would be so much better if I didn't have to write any type of paper ever! All the assignments that my teachers have given me to write about are completely stupid and have absolutely no point. They're just a huge waste of time. At least I don't have to start writing the longer ones for about another month or so. I can't wait til it's all done for another semester. I have to say though that going three days a week is much better than 5. The week goes by so much faster!
Today would not be a good day to be on my bad side because I feel like complete crap!!!

I don't remember ever hating school as much as I do this year. I don't even want to think about getting out of bed to go. The scary thing is that the other day I actually thought about quitting school and working at Stop and Shop for the rest of my life. I must really hate school to really be thinking about working there because the majority of the customers there suck!!!
school... do I have to say anymore?

I'm in love...

There is only one happiness in life,
to love and be loved. <3

I can't believe that today is the last day of August! I am really not ready for all the school work that I'm going to have to do and the boring classes that I am going to have to go to. This is definately one of those summers that I will never never forget... so many things happened. These were the best 3 months that I have had in a long time even with all their ups and downs!

If I know what love is, it is because of you. <3

I went to the bookstore at school the other day and bought my books... $417 later I had all but one book. I wasn't totally surprised because I was expecting it to cost that much. Those books probably cost 50 cents to make and they charge like 75 dollars for a USED book. It's unbelievable! I'm really not looking forward to school starting up again. This summer has been so much fun... probably the best summer I have had in a very long time. I'm not ready to go back to the papers and reading assignments and all that other good stuff. The only things that I'm looking forward to is my birthday and Christmas. School hasn't even started yet and I can't wait for it to be over!!!
I went to the beach yesterday with Judy, Val, and Anna. It was alot of fun! The worst part is that my back burnt. So now it hurts to wear shirts or sleep on my back. :(

Went to the red sox game last night. It was a good game but long and hot. It would have been so much better but the red sox blew their big lead and still managed to win. Drunk people are really funny at sporting events lol!!!!I didn't get home until 1:45am. It was a long day. Over all it was a good time.
